  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3181a2b2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 09 · Preprocesamiento para Clasificación\n",
    "\n",
    "Separación `X`/`y`, codificación, división estratificada train/test 80-20.\n",
    "Se usa `Pipeline` para evitar fuga de datos (el preprocesamiento se aplica solo sobre train).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "952f09f1",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.272231Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.272111Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.279397Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.278477Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Clases codificadas:\n",
      "  0: Insufficient_Weight\n",
      "  1: Normal_Weight\n",
      "  2: Obesity_Type_I\n",
      "  3: Obesity_Type_II\n",
      "  4: Obesity_Type_III\n",
      "  5: Overweight_Level_I\n",
      "  6: Overweight_Level_II\n",
      "\n",
      "Train: 1688 registros\n",
      "Test : 423 registros\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# X e y (sin columna Cluster que se creó en el paso anterior)\n",
    "X = df[COLS_NUM + COLS_CAT].copy()\n",
    "y_raw = df[TARGET].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Codificar variable objetivo\n",
    "le_target = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "y = le_target.fit_transform(y_raw)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Clases codificadas:')\n",
    "for i, cls in enumerate(le_target.classes_):\n",
    "    print(f'  {i}: {cls}')\n",
    "\n",
    "# División train/test estratificada\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f'\\nTrain: {X_train.shape[0]} registros')\n",
    "print(f'Test : {X_test.shape[0]} registros')\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "b481cc72",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.282512Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.282094Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.286834Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.285929Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Modelos definidos: ['Regresión Logística', 'Árbol de Decisión', 'Random Forest', 'KNN', 'SVM', 'XGBoost']\n",
      "SVM se incorpora en la Iteración 3 para cumplir los modelos mínimos del PRD §13.1.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Preprocesador dentro de Pipeline (evita data leakage)\n",
    "preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=[\n",
    "    ('num', StandardScaler(), COLS_NUM),\n",
    "    ('cat', OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value', unknown_value=-1), COLS_CAT)\n",
    "], remainder='drop')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Definición de modelos\n",
    "# XGBoost se incluye porque: (1) domina benchmarks tabulares, (2) maneja\n",
    "# variables mixtas codificadas, (3) permite comparar contra ensembles de\n",
    "# bibliografía reciente que usa este mismo dataset (Das et al., 2026).\n",
    "modelos = {\n",
    "    'Regresión Logística'  : LogisticRegression(max_iter=2000, random_state=RANDOM_STATE,\n",
    "                                                 solver='lbfgs'),\n",
    "    'Árbol de Decisión'    : DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=12, random_state=RANDOM_STATE),\n",
    "    'Random Forest'        : RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=RANDOM_STATE,\n",
    "                                                     n_jobs=-1),\n",
    "    'KNN'                  : KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=7, n_jobs=-1),\n",
    "    'SVM'                  : SVC(kernel='rbf', C=10, gamma='scale',\n",
    "                                 random_state=RANDOM_STATE),\n",
    "    'XGBoost'              : XGBClassifier(n_estimators=200, max_depth=6, learning_rate=0.1,\n",
    "                                           random_state=RANDOM_STATE, n_jobs=-1,\n",
    "                                           eval_metric='mlogloss', verbosity=0),\n",
    "}\n",
    "print('Modelos definidos:', list(modelos.keys()))\n",
    "print('SVM se incorpora en la Iteración 3 para cumplir los modelos mínimos del PRD §13.1.')\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "773007b1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10 · Entrenamiento de Modelos de Clasificación"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "id": "244a106a",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.288380Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-06-13T12:46:03.288228Z",
