   "source": [
    "## 15 · Experimento 2 — Reducción de Dimensionalidad con TruncatedSVD\n",
    "\n",
    "**Pregunta del experimento:**\n",
    "> ¿La reducción con TruncatedSVD mejora el desempeño o simplifica el espacio de variables codificadas?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Diseño:**\n",
    "TruncatedSVD es especialmente útil sobre matrices dispersas generadas por **One-Hot Encoding**.\n",
    "A diferencia del flujo base (OrdinalEncoder → 16 columnas), aquí:\n",
    "1. Se codifica con `OneHotEncoder` → la matriz se expande a ~31 columnas binarias\n",
    "2. Se aplica TruncatedSVD para comprimir ese espacio expandido\n",
    "3. Se evalúa clustering (Silhouette) y clasificación (F1 macro, Accuracy)\n",
    "\n",
    "Esto convierte al experimento en una comparación de **dos estrategias de codificación + compresión**.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "id": "95578907",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-06-13T12:46:06.914255Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-06-13T12:46:06.914127Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-06-13T12:46:07.077250Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-06-13T12:46:07.075901Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Matriz One-Hot: 2111 filas × 31 columnas (vs 16 originales)\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Columnas One-Hot               : 31\n",
      "Componentes para 90% varianza  : 11\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def crear_prep_ohe():\n",
    "    \"\"\"ColumnTransformer con OneHotEncoder (espacio expandido para SVD).\"\"\"\n",
    "    return ColumnTransformer(transformers=[\n",
    "        ('num', StandardScaler(), COLS_NUM),\n",
    "        ('cat', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore', sparse_output=False), COLS_CAT),\n",
    "    ], remainder='drop')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Matriz One-Hot completa (solo predictores — sin target, sin fuga)\n",
    "prep_ohe_clust = crear_prep_ohe()\n",
    "X_ohe = prep_ohe_clust.fit_transform(df[COLS_NUM + COLS_CAT])\n",
    "print(f'Matriz One-Hot: {X_ohe.shape[0]} filas × {X_ohe.shape[1]} columnas '\n",
    "      f'(vs {len(COLS_NUM + COLS_CAT)} originales)')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Varianza explicada por componentes SVD\n",
    "svd_full = TruncatedSVD(n_components=X_ohe.shape[1] - 1, random_state=RANDOM_STATE).fit(X_ohe)\n",
    "var_acum_svd = np.cumsum(svd_full.explained_variance_ratio_)\n",
    "n_comp_svd = int(np.argmax(var_acum_svd >= 0.90) + 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 5))\n",
    "ax.plot(range(1, len(var_acum_svd) + 1), var_acum_svd, 'o-', color='#FF5722', linewidth=2)\n",
    "ax.axhline(y=0.90, color='red', linestyle='--', label='90% de varianza')\n",
    "ax.axvline(x=n_comp_svd, color='green', linestyle=':', linewidth=2,\n",
    "           label=f'{n_comp_svd} componentes')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Número de Componentes SVD')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Varianza Explicada Acumulada (aprox.)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Experimento 2 · TruncatedSVD — Varianza Explicada Acumulada')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid(alpha=0.4)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('outputs/13_svd_varianza.png', dpi=120)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Columnas One-Hot               : {X_ohe.shape[1]}')\n",
    "print(f'Componentes para 90% varianza  : {n_comp_svd}')\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 41,
   "id": "f9f17255",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-06-13T12:46:07.078882Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-06-13T12:46:07.078743Z",
